    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'd accept a PR for this that cleans this up a bit:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/8be635b6d7541d68cbe9a58ae8b618c4c73c1b5b/anvil/src/lib.rs#L211-L212\r\n\r\nthis is basically just a select of two joinhandles.\r\n\r\nwe could just keep them as individual fields in the `NodeHandle` instead.\r\n\r\nit also looks like the `NodeService` task doesn't necessarily resolve if the shutdown signal was fired, so perhaps we integrate this via a tokio::select instead\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n   select!{\r\n      shutdown,\r\n      service\r\n  }\r\n```",
